For a dark, single-page site with a custom domain and simple donate/subscribe anchors, Cloudflare Pages is the best default host: the free tier includes unlimited static requests/bandwidth, 500 builds per month, and custom domains, which fits a one-page marketing site very well. Custom domains are first-class in Pages.  ￼

For donations, the two best options are:
	•	Ko-fi if you want the fastest creator-style support flow; it pays directly to your PayPal or Stripe account and is easy to embed/link.  ￼
	•	Stripe Payment Links if you want the cleanest branded payment flow and full control. Stripe supports one-time payments, subscriptions, and tip/donation-style links with no-code hosted checkout pages. But there is one important wording caveat: for non-charity creators, Stripe distinguishes true "donations" from support/tips, so for Beast2 you should usually phrase it as support Beast2 or fund development, not charitable donation.  ￼

My recommendation:

Host: Cloudflare Pages
Domain: beast2.ai on Cloudflare DNS
Subscribe: Buttondown, ConvertKit, or simple email form later; for v1 just collect emails with a plain form or even a mailto/Google Form placeholder
Donate: Stripe Payment Links or Ko-fi
Best v1 donation buttons: $6.66, $66.60, $666

