Yes. For this setup, the clean path is:

Ko-fi for support + Cloudflare Pages via Wrangler for deploy.

Ko-fi is a good fit because payments go directly to your own PayPal or Stripe account, and Ko-fi does not hold creator funds. Their help docs also say you can connect Stripe or PayPal in Settings → Payment.  ￼

For hosting, Cloudflare Pages is a strong fit for this one-page static site. Cloudflare’s docs support direct upload from your local machine with Wrangler, and the Pages CLI command is wrangler pages deploy [DIRECTORY]. Their docs also note direct upload is the right choice when you want to upload prebuilt assets from your local computer.  ￼

Repo structure

Use this:

beast2-ai-site/
  index.html
  README.md

That is enough for v1.

If you want one tiny upgrade:

beast2-ai-site/
  index.html
  README.md
  assets/

Put logo images or future screenshots in assets/.

Copy-paste setup for Cursor terminal

Run this on your desktop in Cursor terminal:

mkdir beast2-ai-site
cd beast2-ai-site
printf '%s\n' '# beast2.ai site' > README.md

Then place your index.html in that folder.

If you already have the HTML file somewhere else:

mkdir beast2-ai-site
mv beast2_ai_single_page.html beast2-ai-site/index.html
cd beast2-ai-site
printf '%s\n' '# beast2.ai site' > README.md

Git init and push

Replace YOUR_GITHUB_USERNAME below.

cd beast2-ai-site
git init
git add .
git commit -m "init beast2.ai landing page"
gh repo create beast2-ai-site --public --source=. --remote=origin --push

If you are not using GitHub CLI:

cd beast2-ai-site
git init
git add .
git commit -m "init beast2.ai landing page"
git branch -M main
git remote add origin git@github.com:YOUR_GITHUB_USERNAME/beast2-ai-site.git
git push -u origin main

Cloudflare Pages deploy command

First deploy:

npx wrangler pages deploy . --project-name beast2-ai

That command is directly supported by Cloudflare’s Pages docs.  ￼

After that, for updates:

git add .
git commit -m "update site"
git push
npx wrangler pages deploy . --project-name beast2-ai

What to do in Cloudflare

After first deploy:
	1.	Create or log into Cloudflare.
	2.	Authenticate Wrangler if prompted.
	3.	In Pages, connect the custom domain beast2.ai.
	4.	Point your DNS there.

Cloudflare Pages supports custom domains, and direct upload is meant for this local upload workflow.  ￼

What to do in Ko-fi

Create your Ko-fi page, connect Stripe or PayPal, then drop your Ko-fi link into the donate buttons in index.html. Ko-fi’s docs say creators connect their own payment method and get paid directly.  ￼

For your buttons, use:
